Soft Reset: Codes of Calm

After the boldness, a breath.
This isn’t about trends or statements, it’s a quiet return to self.
Jewellery placed back in its tray. Perfume lids clicked closed. Coco codes intact….
The adventure winds down with a whisper of powder and pastel.

Iridescence and blush. Satin and stillness.

Which code do you return to when you reset?

latestPosts.caption:
Two Frequencies: The Legacy & the Find

Some pieces are quiet — they linger, shimmer, stay close to the skin.
Others arrive with force — a bold brushstroke, a memory in motion.

Today, I found both.

A graffiti bomber from Karl’s final pre-fall: loud, unapologetic, and pulsing with the energy of 80s rebellion.
And a fine jewellery piece — quiet, glinting, unmistakably eternal. A Coco whisper caught in gold.

One was waiting for me in the light. The other waited for me to return.
Not a checklist. Not a trend. Just a code — recognised, remembered.

Which one would you call yours — the loud memory or the quiet glimmer? 🖤

latestPosts.caption:
The Collector’s Frequency: CC Codes in Focus

When I say I collect codes, this is what I mean.
Leather, tweed, graffiti, pop art (painted by me)— each piece holds a different note, but somehow they all belong to the same rhythm. I never really chose these at random; I followed the codes that kept repeating back to me.

It’s never just a bag. It’s how you build a language of style.

Which one would you hang first on your shoulder? 🖤

latestPosts.caption:
The Codes Shift: Tweed After Dark.

Some pieces arrive quietly and start writing their own chapters.
This black and white sequinned tweed has slipped into my evening codes — textured, structured, softened by the quiet movement of feathers.

The trousers came later. Unplanned. But somehow, always meant to pair.
With my classic flap, it forms a language I return to: contrast, balance, and a trace of that 80s silhouette I always carry with me.

Which piece would you restyle your way? ✨

Each layer returns with new rhythm: a cuff, a bag, a jacket re-read under different light. This isn’t about trends. It’s the quiet repetition of codes that build a personal archive.

Summer Contrasts: A CC Code
Summer invites lightness — but not always simplicity.

Some pieces cool the eye while carrying warmth beneath. A jacket that glows softly in the sun. A bag that holds its own against pale skies. Texture that speaks when colour whispers.

This is how I build my summer rhythm: by pairing contrasts that don’t compete — they balance.

Do you shift your textures as the seasons turn?

The Rhythm of Blue: A CC Code
In my wardrobe, blue has always carried a quiet energy. A strength that doesn’t demand attention. Calm that holds movement beneath the surface.
A Goossens cuff. A mirrored lipstick case. A tweed bag that hints of northern fields.
I don’t collect for seasons. I build for rhythm.
Would you wear tweed in summer?
